						<summary>

						<p>Stone lying in the backyard of the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Dhruva (?), circa 9th century.</p>						

						<p>This damaged and incomplete record refer to <hi rend="bold">Durggamar-Eṟeappa</hi> as governing the territory spread out from Nariyanūr to Kiṟudoṟe when <hi rend="bold">• • varsha</hi> was ruling the territory. The chief must be identical with <hi rend="bold">Duggamāra Eṟeyappa,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Śrīpurusha</hi> of the <hi rend="bold">Gaṅga</hi> family, in which case the king has to be identified with <hi rend="bold">Dhārāvarsha Dhruva.</hi> All other details of the record are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
